The paper deals with streaming algorithms for language recognition problems, which are typically studied in the areas of data structures (cs.DS), communication complexity (cs.CC), formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL), machine learning (cs.LG), and information theory (cs.IT). The paper presents results for several different language classes, including \DLIN, \LL$(k)$, and \DCFL, which are all relevant to these sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses techniques from randomized algorithms, which are commonly studied in the areas of machine learning and information theory.
